        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="jYgu-oSVlayiNDzByuDm-38" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;fontSize=16;fontStyle=5" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Deployment Diagram for Secure Video Streaming Infrastructure&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="490" x="180" y="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="jYgu-oSVlayiNDzByuDm-39" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;fontSize=16;" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Description:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;The infrastructure utilizes a distributed cloud architecture to ensure high availability and performance. The Client Device communicates with a Load Balancer via HTTPS protocol, and this communicates with an Application Server. In line with scalability and isolation as defined in Part 1, the core services of API Gateway, Auth, and Streaming are executed as Docker containers on the execution environment of Application Server. Data persistence is achieved via a Database Server located in a secure tier and utilizing SQL/JDBC protocols. To improve the user experience, high-bandwidth video files are offloaded to a Content Delivery Network (CDN) to enable the client to stream media directly from the network edge via HLS/DASH protocols.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="645" x="108" y="700" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
